Updating an existing map and creating a new map are rather different things, so you may want to have two separate methods for these tasks:
```java
public static &lt;K, V&gt; Map&lt;K, V&gt; newMap(V value, K ... keys) {
    return Arrays.stream(keys)
            .distinct()
            .collect(Collectors.toMap(
                k -&gt; k,
                k -&gt; value
            ));
}

public static&lt;K, V&gt; void updateMap(Map&lt;K, V&gt; mutableMap, V value, K ... keys) {
    mutableMap.putAll(newMap(value, keys));
}
```

